AB  - Recently, Cameron (1987) examined the estimation of regression models in which the dependent variable is grouped. One portion of her study considers the estimation of linear normal regression models. Cameron presents Monte Carlo evidence comparing least squares estimation to maximum likelihood estimation. This paper demonstrates that Cameron's Monte Carlo results for normal linear regression models can be obtained analytically by using approximations.
